---
title: Deviled Egg Salad
source: https://www.americastestkitchen.com/recipes/12166-deviled-egg-salad
notes: For a smaller batch, use 6 eggs and 75g mayo.
---

Place @hard-cooked eggs{8} in a #large bowl{}. Add @mayonnaise{1/2%cup}, @Dijon mustard{1%tbsp}, @Tabasco{2%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{1/2%tsp}. Using a #pastry cutter{}, chop and mix until egg whites are rough 1/4-inch pieces and yolks are blended into the dressing.

Stir in @minced celery{1/4%cup} (optional), @chopped dill pickles{1/4%cup}, and @Mama Lil's peppers{10} (chopped). Taste and adjust seasoning. Serve on bread or crackers.
